Probability: 5% chance the price will be higher The end-of-day price of Dogecoin on 15 March 2021 will not be higher as compared to the end-of-day price on 15 February 2021.  On 15 February 2021, the end-of-day price of Dogecoin was $0.058727. In the twenty days since, the end-of-day price has only gone above 15 February’s on one occasion, 18 February.  Even with two major announcements this week supporting the use of Dogecoin, there has not been an increase in value that matches or surpasses the 15 February price of $0.058727 (“Dogecoin Price Index”). CoinFlip announced that Dogecoin can now be purchased with cash at any of their 1,800 ATMs on 2 March and the end-of-day price was $0.050441. Mark Cuban announced on 4 March that the Dallas Mavericks will begin accepting Dogecoin for tickets and merchandise; the end-of-price that day was $0.050453 (Reynolds).  Dogecoin has some history of having social media pump up the value. In July 2020, a viral TikTok video caused a price increase of 35%, followed by a drop of over 60%. The recent high of 7 February 2021 of $0.082605, prompted by Reddit subreddits and tweets from Elon Musk, had already dropped to $0.058727 by February 15 – a 28.9% decrease. “The Dogecoin’s Relative Strength Indicator, a momentum oscillator that measures an asset’s speed and change of price movements, alerted about heavily overbought levels. That amounted to a deeper downside correction in the sessions ahead… The volumes also subsided, putting doubts over the rally’s extension in the sessions ahead” (Gola). While the price could be swung upward by another tweet or social media sensation, those have not happened frequently, and the current trend is headed downward. Since the price has only been above the 15 February 2021 price once in the past 20 days, I forecast a 5% possibility that it will close at a higher rate nine days from now. Sources: “Dogecoin Price Index and Live Chart”. Coindesk. https://www.coindesk.com/price/dogecoin. Accessed March 6, 2021. Gola, Yashu. “Dogecoin Explodes 1, 100% in Gamestop-Like Copycat Rally.” Bitcoinist. January 29, 2021. https://bitcoinist.com/dogecoin-explodes-1100-in-gamestop-like-copycat-rally/. Accessed March 6, 2021. Reynolds, Kevin. “DOGE Adoption on the Rise. Dallas Mavericks to Accept Dogecoin for Tickets, Merchandise.” Coindesk. March 4, 2021. https://www.coindesk.com/git-along-lil-doge-dallas-mavs-toaccept-dogecoin-for-tickets-merchandise. Accessed March 6, 2021.

Looking at the exchange rate of DOGE/BTC since 29 Jan 2021, there are some assessments,
/DOGE has broken a 0.00000100BTC rate (100 "Satoshis" (sat)) for the first time on 29 January 2021 for the first time, and showed a strong trend towards 200sat until 
/on 08 Feb 2021 the trend temporarily reversed and DOGE fell to 100sat around ten days later (17 Feb 2021)
/after 17 Feb 2021, it meandered around 100sat until 24 Feb 2021, increasing to a band of 100 -115sat after 24 Feb 2021
/it has at no point fallen below 100sat since, but is currently traded at 100sat. Bitcoin as a reference to the whole market has recovered from the recent major pullback and is traded at >50kUSD again, and it is reasonable to believe that "Altcoins" lag behind in the recovery but will ultimately follow. 
Even though at the Senate hearing of Mr Wray (Director FBI) there was also talk about the role that crypto currencies potentially play in financing terror, security threats and enabling "cyber crime" in general, it seems this risk to the crypto asset market is already priced in and the hearing will not have immediate consequence with respect to regulatory action (e.g. halting trading, prohibiting assets or similar), the more so because it's still unclear apparently whether "Altcoins" are to be classified as an "asset", as a commodity, as money, or as a security.
Assumed BTC is not falling below 50,000USD over the next 14 days again, odds are high DOGE will make a jump to at least 0.06USD/0.00000120BTC or more and the question will resolve "yes".

2021 has been a weird year for equity markets. People sitting on piles of cash acquired through: staying at home and cutting large expenses like travel, federal stimulus cheques, an explosion of retail stock trading platforms, and IMO a general level of boredom in lockdowns. DC got a huge boost around the same time as the Gamestop story picked up steam. Around the same time other crypto currencies began picking up steam (BTC and E-Coin from Ethereum being the easiest names in the business). The wave has looked to lose steam after Elon's tweet promoting the coin, but who knows what the future month holds as people are both super optimistic/pessemistic about the economy (seems were past/in/beginning recovery depending on how you ask) and markets have become increasingly volatile. I want to believe the masses have lost the flame that is Dogecoin as a store of value, but I will hedge my bet by 1/3 odds.
